t: Praise*p ye the Lord.*s Sing unto the Lord*s a new song, and his praise in the congregation of saints.
Let*p Israel rejoice in him that made him: let the children of Zion be joyful in their King.
Let*p them praise his name in the dance: let them sing praises unto him with the timbrel and harp.
For*p the Lord*s taketh pleasure in his people: he will beautify the meek with salvation.
Let*p the saints be joyful in glory: let them sing aloud upon their beds.
Let*p the high praises of God be in their mouth, and a twoedged sword in their hand;
To*p execute vengeance upon the heathen, and punishments upon the people;
To*p bind their kings with chains, and their nobles with fetters of iron;
To*p execute upon them the judgment written: this honour have all his saints. Praise ye the Lord.*s
